                        <h4 style="color: #337ab7">LIVING SANT SAT GURU</h4>
                        &emsp;&emsp;In the Radhasoami Faith, great is the importance of the Sant Sat Guru of the time.
                        <br />&emsp;&emsp;“When the Sat Guru of the time departs, He appoints someone as His successor
                        in
                        whom He re-incarnates and thus continues the work of regeneration of Jivas as
                        before……….Therefore,
                        an earnest devotee should make no distinction between the previous Sat Guru and His successor.
                        But
                        those who are bigoted devotees will not come under the allegiance to the succeeding Sat Guru.
                        For this reason, their progress will also stop at the stage they had reached during the time of
                        the
                        former Sat Guru and there would be no further progress and improvement”.
                        (Sar Bachan Radhasoami, Prose, Part-2, Bachan-250)
                        <br />&emsp;&emsp;The Sant Sat Guru of the time while present on this plane, may choose not to
                        ‘manifest’
                        immediately. When the Sant Sat Guru of the time is not manifested, there is a period of
                        Interregnum, so to say.
                        Interregnum does not mean that He is not present. He is indeed present but during Interregnum He
                        does not grant
                        His recognition, therefore people do not know His identity. When it is His Mauj, He grants
                        recognition to
                        Adhikari (fit) Jivas. Gradually others also become aware and associate themselves with Him.
                        Indeed, it would not be right to say that there has been no Sant Sat Guru all these years in
                        Radhasoami
                        Satsang, Soamibagh, Agra. The Sant Sat Guru has been present all this time, and He is very much
                        present.
                        He Himself gives His own recognition at the proper time. Those who regularly and daily perform
                        spiritual
                        practices (Sumiran, Dhyan, and Bhajan) do come to know about it internally in the fullness of
                        time.
                        Reliable proof or indication can be had only in the course of performing internal practices.
                        “Till one receives an unmistakable proof within oneself of the manifestation of the Sant Sat
                        Guru, one
                        had better continue to stick to the form of the last Sant Sat Guru.
                        There is no time limit for such a manifestation. It all depends upon His Mauj or the Divine
                        Will.
                        But there should not be any doubt in one’s mind that the divine current is or will ever be
                        withdrawn
                        from this plane, till the redemption of the entire creation has been affected. Hence, having
                        full
